text:
Why does the import > replace feature never work as it is intended? It always adds new rows, it does not replace existing rows. The icon/option on import clearly states "Replace all rows in the HubDB table with rows from the file."

Even if we try to map the three 'hs_' columns. Can we get this fixed ASAP please?! It's been an issue for over a month now. Creating a new table every time is NOT an option, there are too many pages/coded files relying on the table ID to go back and change them to a new ID every time we need to bulk update a table.
At minimum, please allow the option to bulk delete all rows in the table, right now you can only delete one row at a time, or add one at a time.
We have been told it is out of Beta, and yet a Replace feature does nothing but Add rows. <@U22PJPGK0> <@U22PU4G4A> <@U22PKFRU5>
<@U26CZR9MW> thanks for letting us know. the replace functionality should work now.
<@U22VBL87M> its not fixed. it went from 211 to 422 rows. yes I cleared my cache first. is anyone testing this stuff before it is released?
<@U26CZR9MW>: we try our best. It looks like replacing table data is now working, but the count of rows is off. We'll fix that soon.

<@U22PJPGK0> thank you. I understand, been doing this long enough.  Regardless of proper testing, it is working, thank you team HubDb. No worries, we are one step closer now right? :slightly_smiling_face:
I think so. The row count is really only for convenience in the editor. It has no bearing on the actual rows returned.
<@U26CZR9MW> pinned a message to this channel.
